cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper is about cross-modal information retrieval, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a dual-path neural network model for feature learning, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper uses word2vec and graph convolutional network (GCN) for text modeling, which are both related to artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
